1
00:00:31,916 --> 00:00:33,458
- ( theme music playing )

2
00:00:43,875 --> 00:00:45,583
- ( woman singing in Japanese )

3
00:02:03,250 --> 00:02:04,833
- ( sirens blaring )

4
00:02:07,916 --> 00:02:09,458
- THIS IS THE GALAXY POLICE.

5
00:02:09,541 --> 00:02:10,541
YOU ARE COMPLETELY SURROUNDED.

6
00:02:10,625 --> 00:02:12,666
YOU HAVE ONE MINUTE
TO SURRENDER.

7
00:02:15,000 --> 00:02:16,000
- ( all screaming )

8
00:02:25,041 --> 00:02:26,416
- ( coughs )
HUH?

9
00:02:26,500 --> 00:02:28,083
- YOU GUYS ARE
REALLY PATHETIC.

10
00:02:28,166 --> 00:02:30,208
YOU DON'T THINK WE PLANNED
AN ESCAPE ROUTE?

11
00:02:30,291 --> 00:02:31,333
TIME TO SPLIT, BOYS.

12
00:02:31,416 --> 00:02:32,375
- ( men cheering )

13
00:02:37,500 --> 00:02:39,583
- READY DOWN HERE.
HOTSUMA!

14
00:02:44,291 --> 00:02:46,958
- ( all cheer )

15
00:02:48,458 --> 00:02:49,916
- ( groans )

16
00:02:50,000 --> 00:02:50,916
( grunts )

17
00:02:52,958 --> 00:02:54,875
( groans )

18
00:02:57,166 --> 00:02:59,750
- ( chuckles )

19
00:02:59,833 --> 00:03:00,958
( laughs )

20
00:03:03,625 --> 00:03:06,000
IF THEY MAKE IT ANY EASIER
TO WIN THESE LITTLE SKIRMISHES,

21
00:03:06,083 --> 00:03:08,708
I MAY HAVE TO RETIRE FROM
SPACE PIRACY OUT OF BOREDOM.

22
00:03:08,791 --> 00:03:10,166
- YOU WERE REALLY AMAZING.

23
00:03:10,250 --> 00:03:12,250
- YOUR BOYS PERFORMED
VERY WELL, HOTSUMA.

24
00:03:12,333 --> 00:03:13,666
I THINK THEY
DESERVE A REWARD.

25
00:03:13,750 --> 00:03:15,333
LET'S GET BACK
TO THE HIDEOUT.

26
00:03:15,416 --> 00:03:17,083
WE'LL HAVE A PARTY
TO CELEBRATE.

27
00:03:17,166 --> 00:03:18,250
- ( cheering )

28
00:03:18,333 --> 00:03:20,416
- Mihoshi: YEAH, OKAY!
TIME TO GET CRAZY.

29
00:03:20,500 --> 00:03:23,000
LET'S PARTY HEARTY!
KNOCK OURSELVES OUT.

30
00:03:23,083 --> 00:03:24,250
I-- ( grunts )
- Kiyone: MIHOSHI!

31
00:03:24,333 --> 00:03:26,583
HAVE YOU GONE NUTS?
REMEMBER WHO WE ARE.

32
00:03:26,666 --> 00:03:28,583
- I'M SORRY.  I FORGOT.

33
00:03:28,666 --> 00:03:30,416
- RYOKO...

34
00:03:30,500 --> 00:03:32,000
I NEVER IMAGINED
THERE'D COME A DAY

35
00:03:32,083 --> 00:03:33,500
THAT I'D HAVE TO ARREST YOU.

36
00:03:33,583 --> 00:03:36,375
- ( Ryoko laughs )

37
00:03:44,583 --> 00:03:46,500
- ( locusts chirping )

38
00:03:53,666 --> 00:03:55,583
- YOU HAVE 30 MINUTES
TO FINISH THE EXAM.

39
00:03:55,666 --> 00:03:57,125
WORK QUICKLY.

40
00:03:57,208 --> 00:04:00,083
- AAH!  I DON'T KNOW
THE ANSWERS TO ANYTHING.

41
00:04:02,208 --> 00:04:03,791
- ( sighs )

42
00:04:03,875 --> 00:04:06,708
Tenchi: I NEVER THOUGHT
THEY HAD LOCUSTS IN TOKYO.

43
00:04:06,791 --> 00:04:08,000
- ( chirping )

44
00:04:09,708 --> 00:04:11,291
- ( bell tolling )
- ALL RIGHT, EVERYBODY.

45
00:04:11,375 --> 00:04:12,375
TIME'S UP.

46
00:04:12,458 --> 00:04:14,166
COLLECT THE SHEETS
AND PASS THEM IN.

47
00:04:14,250 --> 00:04:15,500
- ( students murmur )

48
00:04:16,708 --> 00:04:18,500
- ( groans )
THAT'S OVER.

49
00:04:18,583 --> 00:04:19,791
- SO WHAT DO YOU THINK?

50
00:04:19,875 --> 00:04:21,333
HOW DID YOU DO?
DID YOU PASS IT?

51
00:04:21,416 --> 00:04:23,333
- SURE, IT WASN'T
TOO BAD NOW, WAS IT?

52
00:04:23,416 --> 00:04:26,250
- DOES THE NAME "TITANIC"
MEAN ANYTHING TO YOU?

53
00:04:26,333 --> 00:04:27,666
- DID YOU ACE IT,
PROFESSOR?

54
00:04:27,750 --> 00:04:29,333
- I THINK I DID SO-SO.

55
00:04:29,416 --> 00:04:31,291
- I THINK AMAGASAKI
AND I ARE GONNA HAVE TO

56
00:04:31,375 --> 00:04:32,958
TRY AGAIN WITH
A MAKE-UP EXAM.

57
00:04:33,041 --> 00:04:34,625
- WHAT FOR?
- WHAT'S THE POINT?

58
00:04:34,708 --> 00:04:36,291
I WON'T DO BETTER
ON A REPEAT.

59
00:04:36,375 --> 00:04:37,291
- ( cries )

60
00:04:37,375 --> 00:04:38,583
- THERE GOES
MY SUMMER VACATION.

61
00:04:38,666 --> 00:04:40,500
- I'M GLAD THAT'S OVER.

62
00:04:40,583 --> 00:04:42,208
- YEP.  DID YOU HAVE
ANY TROUBLE WITH IT?

63
00:04:42,291 --> 00:04:43,291
- NOT REALLY.

64
00:04:43,375 --> 00:04:44,333
- ( groans )
- OH, BROTHER.

65
00:04:44,416 --> 00:04:46,000
- NO.
- NOT EVERYBODY HERE'S

66
00:04:46,083 --> 00:04:47,625
A BRAINIAC.
- WHAT'S THE BIG DEAL?

67
00:04:47,708 --> 00:04:49,500
ALL WE DID WAS PASS.
- I MEAN, COME ON.

68
00:04:49,583 --> 00:04:50,875
WE'RE NOT REALLY
THAT BRILLIANT.

69
00:04:50,958 --> 00:04:52,333
- Sakuya and Tenchi:
RIGHT?

70
00:04:52,416 --> 00:04:53,541
- ( all groan )

71
00:04:54,708 --> 00:04:56,166
- I'M BORED WITH ALL THIS.

72
00:04:56,250 --> 00:04:57,625
NOW THAT EXAMS ARE OVER,

73
00:04:57,708 --> 00:04:58,833
WHY DON'T WE ALL
TAKE A BREAK

74
00:04:58,916 --> 00:05:00,833
AND GO SOMEPLACE
FUN FOR AWHILE?

75
00:05:00,916 --> 00:05:02,875
- WHAT DO YOU MEAN?
- IT'S SUMMER VACATION.

76
00:05:02,958 --> 00:05:04,250
WE SHOULD GO ON
A TRIP SOMEWHERE.

77
00:05:04,333 --> 00:05:06,041
WHAT DO YOU THINK?
- DON'T KNOW.

78
00:05:06,125 --> 00:05:07,875
- SOUNDS GOOD.
- WHERE SHOULD WE GO?

79
00:05:07,958 --> 00:05:09,833
- DID I ASK YOU TO COME?

80
00:05:09,916 --> 00:05:11,041
- YOU'RE SUCH A PIG.

81
00:05:11,125 --> 00:05:12,458
IT'S SO SIMPLE.

82
00:05:12,541 --> 00:05:14,708
WHEREVER TENCHI GOES,
SAKUYA WILL GO WITH HIM, RIGHT?

83
00:05:14,791 --> 00:05:17,208
- RIGHT.
( giggles )

84
00:05:17,291 --> 00:05:18,708
- ALL RIGHT.
EVERYBODY'S GOING.

85
00:05:18,791 --> 00:05:20,166
TENCHI, YOU PICK THE PLACE.

86
00:05:20,250 --> 00:05:21,458
- WHY ME, GUYS?

87
00:05:21,541 --> 00:05:23,208
- BECAUSE THIS WILL BE
YOUR FIRST SUMMER BREAK

88
00:05:23,291 --> 00:05:24,875
IN TOKYO.
WE SHOULD GO SOMEWHERE

89
00:05:24,958 --> 00:05:26,000
YOU HAVEN'T SEEN.

90
00:05:26,083 --> 00:05:27,708
- AND BESIDES,
ALL THINGS BEING EQUAL,

91
00:05:27,791 --> 00:05:29,000
WE TRUST YOUR JUDGMENT.

92
00:05:29,083 --> 00:05:30,208
- WHAT DO YOU MEAN BY THAT?

93
00:05:30,291 --> 00:05:31,208
- Girls:
IT'S OBVIOUS.

94
00:05:31,291 --> 00:05:32,375
- WE DON'T TRUST YOU.

95
00:05:32,458 --> 00:05:34,375
- Girls: COME ON, TENCHI.
CHOOSE.

96
00:05:34,458 --> 00:05:36,250
- Tenchi: UH, WELL...
- Amagasaki: COME ON, BUDDY.

97
00:05:36,333 --> 00:05:38,166
- Tsuchida: WE HAVEN'T GOT
ALL DAY, YOU KNOW?

98
00:05:38,250 --> 00:05:40,333
- Sakuya: IT'S AMAZING.
PEOPLE ARE DRAWN TO TENCHI

99
00:05:40,416 --> 00:05:41,666
LIKE A MAGNET.

100
00:05:41,750 --> 00:05:44,625
I SHOULDN'T BE SURPRISED.
I FEEL THE SAME WAY.

101
00:05:44,708 --> 00:05:47,583
- MAKING PLANS TO GET AWAY
FOR SOME FUN THIS SUMMER.  YEP.

102
00:05:47,666 --> 00:05:49,416
MAKES ME WISH I WAS
17 AGAIN.

103
00:05:49,500 --> 00:05:51,958
EXCEPT FOR THE ZITS
AND BEING GROUNDED ALL THE TIME.

104
00:06:02,375 --> 00:06:04,666
- ( men chattering )

105
00:06:10,458 --> 00:06:11,708
- AHH.

106
00:06:11,791 --> 00:06:12,958
( chuckles )

107
00:06:13,041 --> 00:06:14,500
THIS BOOZE TASTES
A WHOLE LOT BETTER

108
00:06:14,583 --> 00:06:15,750
IN A STOLEN CUP.

109
00:06:15,833 --> 00:06:18,416
LET YOUR HAIR DOWN
AND GET CRAZY, EVERYBODY.

110
00:06:18,500 --> 00:06:20,250
AND DRINK ALL YOU WANT.
YOU EARNED IT.

111
00:06:20,333 --> 00:06:21,541
- ( cheering )

112
00:06:21,625 --> 00:06:22,708
- WHAT'S WITH YOU?

113
00:06:22,791 --> 00:06:24,041
YOU GOT SOMETHING
YOU WANT TO SAY?

114
00:06:24,125 --> 00:06:26,291
- I WAS THINKING WHAT
A GOOD TEAM WE MAKE

115
00:06:26,375 --> 00:06:27,375
AND HOW WE SHOULD
KEEP IT GOING.

116
00:06:27,458 --> 00:06:28,333
WHAT DO YOU SAY?

117
00:06:29,458 --> 00:06:31,250
- OH.
I'LL DRINK TO THAT.

118
00:06:35,375 --> 00:06:37,625
- Kiyone: WELL WELL,
OUR ANONYMOUS INFORMANT

119
00:06:37,708 --> 00:06:39,125
WAS RIGHT AFTER ALL.

120
00:06:39,208 --> 00:06:40,750
TERRIFIC.

121
00:06:40,833 --> 00:06:42,291
A DETECTIVE'S DREAM.

122
00:06:42,375 --> 00:06:44,625
ALL RIGHT.
I'LL FINALLY GET PROMOTED.

123
00:06:44,708 --> 00:06:45,750
( chuckles )

124
00:06:45,833 --> 00:06:47,375
I CAN MAKE LIEUTENANT!

125
00:06:47,458 --> 00:06:48,625
- All: HUH?

126
00:06:48,708 --> 00:06:50,125
- DRINK UP!
- ( cheering )

127
00:06:50,208 --> 00:06:51,958
- I GOTTA BE MORE CAREFUL
WITH WHAT I SAY

128
00:06:52,041 --> 00:06:53,083
AND DO AROUND HERE.

129
00:06:53,166 --> 00:06:54,625
AND I'D BETTER
CHECK ON MIHOSHI.

130
00:06:54,708 --> 00:06:56,791
SHE'S MORE LIKELY TO BLOW
OUR COVER THAN I AM.

131
00:06:56,875 --> 00:06:58,333
NOW WHERE IS SHE?
( gasps )

132
00:06:58,416 --> 00:07:00,291
- HERE'S MY GALAXY
POLICE DANCE.

133
00:07:00,375 --> 00:07:01,625
( giggles )
THEY'LL BE COMING

134
00:07:01,708 --> 00:07:03,416
TO GET YOU IN A SPACESHIP,
SWEETIE.

135
00:07:03,500 --> 00:07:05,583
( giggles )
- IDIOT!

136
00:07:07,333 --> 00:07:09,708
WHAT'S THE MATTER WITH YOU?
DON'T YOU KNOW WHY WE'RE HERE?!

137
00:07:09,791 --> 00:07:11,166
- WELL, SURE I DO.

138
00:07:11,250 --> 00:07:12,458
WE'RE HERE TO SERVE

139
00:07:12,541 --> 00:07:15,375
THE BEST SPACE PIRATE
IN THE UNIVERSE, RYOKO.

140
00:07:15,458 --> 00:07:16,791
- NO, WE'RE NOT!

141
00:07:16,875 --> 00:07:18,916
DON'T YOU REMEMBER
WE'RE GALAXY POLICE DETECTIVES!

142
00:07:19,000 --> 00:07:20,166
POLICE DETECTIVES!

143
00:07:20,250 --> 00:07:22,166
UH...

144
00:07:22,250 --> 00:07:24,000
UH, PARTY!

145
00:07:24,083 --> 00:07:25,125
- ( cheering )

146
00:07:25,208 --> 00:07:27,250
- IT'S TIME TO
BRING IN OUR GUYS.

147
00:07:27,333 --> 00:07:28,833
WE HAVE TO CONTACT
HEADQUARTERS

148
00:07:28,916 --> 00:07:30,666
AND GET A SPECIAL
SWAT TEAM SENT OUT.

149
00:07:30,750 --> 00:07:32,666
- KIYONE, YOU'RE CUTTING OFF
ALL MY AIR.

150
00:07:32,750 --> 00:07:34,250
- SOMEHOW WE'RE GONNA HAVE TO
FIGURE OUT A WAY

151
00:07:34,333 --> 00:07:35,583
TO GET EVERYBODY
IN THE CAVE

152
00:07:35,666 --> 00:07:37,458
UNTIL OUR TROOPS
CAN SURROUND THE PLACE,

153
00:07:37,541 --> 00:07:39,333
GET ME?
- KEEP EVERYBODY IN.

154
00:07:39,416 --> 00:07:41,041
- VERY GOOD.
- ( groans )

155
00:07:41,125 --> 00:07:42,916
( sighs )
HOW COME YOU'RE SO NERVOUS

156
00:07:43,000 --> 00:07:45,250
ABOUT MAKING SURE
WE APPREHEND THESE GUYS?

157
00:07:45,333 --> 00:07:48,250
- IF WE'RE ABLE TO PUT
A STOP TO RYOKO AND HER PIRATES,

158
00:07:48,333 --> 00:07:49,958
AND WE MAKE IT
BACK HOME IN ONE PIECE,

159
00:07:50,041 --> 00:07:51,541
WE'RE DEFINITELY
GONNA GET PROMOTED.

160
00:07:51,625 --> 00:07:53,708
IN FACT, I EXPECT
TO BE MADE LIEUTENANT.

161
00:07:53,791 --> 00:07:55,333
( giggles )

162
00:07:58,166 --> 00:08:00,375
OH-- PARTY DOWN!
- ( cheering )

163
00:08:00,458 --> 00:08:02,625
- IF YOU HARNESSED ALL THE
BRAIN WAVES IN THIS ROOM,

164
00:08:02,708 --> 00:08:04,833
YOU MIGHT BE ABLE TO POWER
A 15-WATT BULB.

165
00:08:04,916 --> 00:08:07,291
- Mihoshi: KIYONE, DON'T YOU
EVER WONDER WHY RYOKO

166
00:08:07,375 --> 00:08:09,541
WENT BACK TO HER LIFE
AS A SPACE PIRATE?

167
00:08:09,625 --> 00:08:11,083
- Kiyone: HUH?
- Mihoshi: I MEAN, WE WERE ALL

168
00:08:11,166 --> 00:08:13,541
HAVING A GOOD TIME TOGETHER
ON EARTH, WEREN'T WE?

169
00:08:13,625 --> 00:08:14,750
- I GUESS SO.

170
00:08:14,833 --> 00:08:16,375
- DO YOU THINK IT'S
BECAUSE OF TENCHI?

171
00:08:16,458 --> 00:08:17,416
- HUH?
- YEAH, REMEMBER

172
00:08:17,500 --> 00:08:18,583
THE HIGH SCHOOL FESTIVAL?

173
00:08:18,666 --> 00:08:20,416
THAT'S WHEN RYOKO
STARTED ACTING STRANGE.

174
00:08:20,500 --> 00:08:21,625
I WONDER IF SOMETHING
HAPPENED

175
00:08:21,708 --> 00:08:22,750
BETWEEN HER AND TENCHI.

176
00:08:22,833 --> 00:08:25,375
- YOU THINK SHE RAN OFF
OUT OF DESPAIR?

177
00:08:25,458 --> 00:08:27,208
WELL, I SUPPOSE
IT'S POSSIBLE.

178
00:08:27,291 --> 00:08:29,416
IT WOULD CERTAINLY
EXPLAIN A LOT OF THINGS.

179
00:08:29,500 --> 00:08:31,250
ON THE OTHER HAND,
IT COULD BE THAT SHE JUST MISSED

180
00:08:31,333 --> 00:08:33,750
STEALING STUFF INSTEAD OF
WORKING FOR A LIVING.

181
00:08:33,833 --> 00:08:35,791
- RIGHT.  BUT IF SOMETHING
HAPPENED WITH TENCHI

182
00:08:35,875 --> 00:08:37,666
THAT MADE HER FEEL
DESPERATE AND CRAZY,

183
00:08:37,750 --> 00:08:39,000
THEN I FEEL SORRY FOR HER.

184
00:08:39,083 --> 00:08:40,208
- I UNDERSTAND.

185
00:08:40,291 --> 00:08:42,416
- THANKS.
I'M REALLY WORRIED, YOU KNOW?

186
00:08:42,500 --> 00:08:44,541
SHE'S SENSITIVE.
CAN WE HELP OUT?

187
00:08:44,625 --> 00:08:45,875
I MEAN,
WE ARE HER FRIENDS.

188
00:08:45,958 --> 00:08:48,000
- IF YOU'RE RIGHT,
SHE DESERVES THAT CHANCE.

189
00:08:48,083 --> 00:08:49,208
I WON'T BRING IN
THE SWAT TEAM

190
00:08:49,291 --> 00:08:50,458
UNTIL WE'VE OBSERVED HER.

191
00:08:50,541 --> 00:08:53,125
- THANKS!  YOU'RE GREAT.
( giggles )

192
00:08:53,208 --> 00:08:54,208
- CUT IT OUT, MIHOSHI.

193
00:08:54,291 --> 00:08:55,541
- YOU TWO BEHIND THE PILLAR,

194
00:08:55,625 --> 00:08:56,750
COME OUT HERE.

195
00:08:56,833 --> 00:08:57,750
- Both: YOU CALLED?

196
00:08:57,833 --> 00:08:59,458
- WAIT A MINUTE,

197
00:08:59,541 --> 00:09:00,791
- OH, NO.
- YIKES, WHAT DO WE DO?

198
00:09:00,875 --> 00:09:02,416
- SHE'S ONTO US.
- OH, THIS IS AWFUL.

199
00:09:02,500 --> 00:09:04,416
- AREN'T YOU THE NEW SERVANTS?

200
00:09:04,500 --> 00:09:05,750
- Both: YES.
- LOOKS TO ME LIKE

201
00:09:05,833 --> 00:09:06,916
YOU'VE BEEN NEGLECTING
YOUR DUTIES

202
00:09:07,000 --> 00:09:08,666
SO YOU CAN PARTY DOWN
WITH THE GUYS.

203
00:09:08,750 --> 00:09:10,791
- THAT'S US.
WE'RE BIG PARTY ANIMALS.

204
00:09:10,875 --> 00:09:12,291
- AND WE'RE VERY SORRY.

205
00:09:12,375 --> 00:09:13,791
- NOT GOOD ENOUGH.
I'M ASSIGNING YOU

206
00:09:13,875 --> 00:09:14,833
TO CLEAN THE HIDEOUT.

207
00:09:14,916 --> 00:09:16,458
- WAIT A MINUTE,
THIS IS A BIG PLACE.

208
00:09:16,541 --> 00:09:17,791
- WE'RE ON IT, MA'AM.

209
00:09:17,875 --> 00:09:19,166
- Both: BYE.

210
00:09:19,250 --> 00:09:21,291
- WHO ARE THEY?
NEVER SEEN THEM BEFORE.

211
00:09:21,375 --> 00:09:23,458
- JUST TWO GIRLS
I PRESSED INTO SERVICE.

212
00:09:23,541 --> 00:09:25,625
THEY'RE STUPID,
BUT THEY KEEP ME ENTERTAINED.

213
00:09:25,708 --> 00:09:29,291
HMM.  TIME TO WORK,
MIHOSHI AND KIYONE.

214
00:09:29,375 --> 00:09:30,625
- ( grunts )

215
00:09:30,708 --> 00:09:31,833
I CAN'T BELIEVE
WE HAVE TO CLEAN

216
00:09:31,916 --> 00:09:33,291
THIS DINGY OLD DUNGEON.

217
00:09:33,375 --> 00:09:34,958
- IT'S BETTER THAN
BEING LOCKED UP IN

218
00:09:35,041 --> 00:09:36,541
THE DINGY OLD DUNGEON.

219
00:09:36,625 --> 00:09:38,375
- Ryoko: YOU'RE NOT MOVING
FAST ENOUGH, YOU SLACKERS.

220
00:09:38,458 --> 00:09:41,125
GUESS I'LL HAVE TO GIVE YOU
A LITTLE POKE IN THE RIBS.

221
00:09:41,208 --> 00:09:42,666
- Both: WHOA!

222
00:09:42,750 --> 00:09:45,708
- WHAT'S GOING ON?
- WE'RE DUSTING!

223
00:09:45,791 --> 00:09:48,125
- ( cheering )
- ( girls screaming )

224
00:09:48,208 --> 00:09:49,500
- HEY, IT'S TIME FOR LUNCH.

225
00:09:49,583 --> 00:09:51,291
HOW ABOUT SERVANT GIRLS
ON A SKEWER?

226
00:09:51,375 --> 00:09:52,791
- OH, IT'S A DEAD END.

227
00:09:52,875 --> 00:09:54,791
- Both: WHOA!

228
00:09:56,583 --> 00:09:57,958
- SINCE YOU'RE NO GOOD
AT CLEANING,

229
00:09:58,041 --> 00:09:59,666
YOU'LL HAVE TO COOK
TONIGHT'S DINNER.

230
00:10:01,041 --> 00:10:02,500
( laughs )

231
00:10:02,583 --> 00:10:04,000
HOPE YOU CAN BARBEQUE.

232
00:10:04,083 --> 00:10:05,291
WE'RE CARNIVORES.

233
00:10:05,375 --> 00:10:07,333
BY THE WAY,
SO'S THE MAIN DISH.

234
00:10:07,416 --> 00:10:09,583
- ( cheering )
- ( girls screaming )

235
00:10:09,666 --> 00:10:11,583
- ( roars )

236
00:10:12,833 --> 00:10:13,833
- YOU'D BETTER HURRY

237
00:10:13,916 --> 00:10:14,958
BEFORE OUR DINNER MAKES

238
00:10:15,041 --> 00:10:16,083
A MEAL OUT OF YOU.

239
00:10:16,166 --> 00:10:17,458
( laughs )

240
00:10:20,958 --> 00:10:22,083
LAUNDRY TIME, FOLKS.

241
00:10:22,166 --> 00:10:23,541
LET'S NOT KEEP
THESE GIRLS WAITING.

242
00:10:23,625 --> 00:10:25,333
HAND OVER YOUR TOPS
AND BOTTOMS.

243
00:10:25,416 --> 00:10:26,791
- ( cheering )

244
00:10:26,875 --> 00:10:28,500
- ( both scream )

245
00:10:28,583 --> 00:10:31,125
WHOA!

246
00:10:33,291 --> 00:10:35,000
- ( laughs )

247
00:10:35,083 --> 00:10:37,541
- THEY DIDN'T PUT IN
FABRIC SOFTENER.

248
00:10:37,625 --> 00:10:39,541
