IS TELL ME

296
00:11:55,250 --> 00:11:57,041
SHE WAS SADISTIC
WHEN WE ROOMED TOGETHER.

297
00:11:57,125 --> 00:11:58,333
- ( laughing )

298
00:12:02,125 --> 00:12:03,541
- ( chuckles )

299
00:12:05,166 --> 00:12:07,708
- ( meows )

300
00:12:11,708 --> 00:12:12,916
- ( meows )

301
00:12:15,958 --> 00:12:17,750
- HERE'S SOME TEA, RYOKO.

302
00:12:17,833 --> 00:12:18,708
- THANKS.

303
00:12:20,250 --> 00:12:22,125
SO, LONG TIME NO SEE.

304
00:12:22,208 --> 00:12:23,750
- REALLY?
- HERE, KIYONE.

305
00:12:23,833 --> 00:12:25,625
OOH!
- YAH YAH YAH YAH!

306
00:12:25,708 --> 00:12:27,083
ARE YOU TRYING
TO KILL ME, GIRL?

307
00:12:27,166 --> 00:12:29,000
MY BUTT'S ALREADY BURNED!
- SORRY.

308
00:12:29,083 --> 00:12:31,416
- ( laughing ) YOU KNOW,
YOU REALLY GET ME GOING,

309
00:12:31,500 --> 00:12:33,333
BOTH OF YOU.
- SO WHEN DID YOU FIGURE

310
00:12:33,416 --> 00:12:33,958
OUT IT WAS US?

311
00:12:34,041 --> 00:12:35,208
- UM...

312
00:12:35,291 --> 00:12:36,333
NOW LET ME SEE.

313
00:12:37,958 --> 00:12:40,500
THIS IS GONNA BE
OUR FIRST RAID TOGETHER.

314
00:12:40,583 --> 00:12:43,000
JUST DO WHAT I TELL YOU,
AND YOU'LL ALL BE RICH.

315
00:12:43,083 --> 00:12:45,916
- ( cheering )
- Both: YAY!

316
00:12:46,000 --> 00:12:47,458
- IT WAS AROUND THEN.

317
00:12:47,541 --> 00:12:48,708
- FROM THE VERY START?!

318
00:12:48,791 --> 00:12:50,375
- SO MUCH FOR
UNDERCOVER WORK, HUH?

319
00:12:50,458 --> 00:12:52,250
- ( yelps )

320
00:12:52,333 --> 00:12:53,916
- ( laughs )

321
00:12:54,000 --> 00:12:56,208
MAYBE YOU'D BETTER STAY HERE
TILL YOUR BUTT HEALS.

322
00:12:56,291 --> 00:12:57,833
- IS IT ALL RIGHT,
REALLY?

323
00:12:57,916 --> 00:12:59,250
IT'S SO COMFORTABLE HERE.

324
00:12:59,333 --> 00:13:00,666
IT'S ALMOST LIKE
WE'RE BACK ON EARTH.

325
00:13:00,750 --> 00:13:02,791
- YEAH.  IT KIND OF
FEELS THAT WAY, DOESN'T IT?

326
00:13:02,875 --> 00:13:05,333
HOTSUMA MADE THIS ROOM
TO MY SPECIFICATIONS.

327
00:13:05,416 --> 00:13:06,375
DIDN'T YOU, HOTSUMA?

328
00:13:06,458 --> 00:13:07,666
HOTSUMA?

329
00:13:07,750 --> 00:13:08,833
NOW WHERE DID HE GO?

330
00:13:08,916 --> 00:13:11,250
HOTSUMA, COME IN HERE.

331
00:13:11,333 --> 00:13:12,458
OH, WELL, HE MUST BE TIED UP.

332
00:13:12,541 --> 00:13:13,583
ANYWAY,
IT'S PRETTY COMFORTABLE,

333
00:13:13,666 --> 00:13:15,000
SO MAKE YOURSELVES AT HOME.

334
00:13:15,083 --> 00:13:16,666
- Mihoshi:
THANKS, RYOKO.  WE WILL.

335
00:13:16,750 --> 00:13:19,250
- TELL ME SOMETHING FIRST.
WHY ARE YOU DOING THIS?

336
00:13:19,333 --> 00:13:20,583
- WHY?  COME ON,

337
00:13:20,666 --> 00:13:22,166
I WAS JUST TEASING YOU
A LITTLE BIT.

338
00:13:22,250 --> 00:13:23,208
I'VE MISSED YOU GUYS.

339
00:13:23,291 --> 00:13:24,375
- THAT'S NOT WHAT I MEANT.

340
00:13:24,458 --> 00:13:26,500
- HEY, MIHOSHI,
WHAT A SURPRISE.

341
00:13:26,583 --> 00:13:28,041
I DIDN'T KNOW YOU COULD
BREATHE FIRE.

342
00:13:28,125 --> 00:13:29,625
- ( giggles )
IT'S ALL BECAUSE OF

343
00:13:29,708 --> 00:13:31,291
THIS MAGIC KIT
I GOT FROM WASHU.

344
00:13:31,375 --> 00:13:34,041
- YOU NEVER TOLD ME SHE GAVE
YOU THAT. WAIT A MINUTE!

345
00:13:34,125 --> 00:13:36,500
HOW COME YOU WENT BACK INTO
THE SPACE PIRATE BUSINESS?

346
00:13:36,583 --> 00:13:38,500
THAT'S WHAT I WANT TO KNOW.
- HUH?

347
00:13:38,583 --> 00:13:41,166
WHAT DO YOU MEAN "WHY DID I GO
BACK TO BEING A SPACE PIRATE?"

348
00:13:41,250 --> 00:13:42,416
THAT'S WHAT I DO
FOR A LIVING,

349
00:13:42,500 --> 00:13:43,500
DON'T MAKE ME LAUGH.

350
00:13:43,583 --> 00:13:45,208
- OKAY, FINE.
THEN LET ME ASK THIS,

351
00:13:45,291 --> 00:13:46,416
WHAT MADE YOU LEAVE EARTH?

352
00:13:46,500 --> 00:13:48,375
- THAT'S NONE OF YOUR BUSINESS,
DETECTIVE.

353
00:13:48,458 --> 00:13:50,208
- SOMETHING HAPPENED
BETWEEN YOU AND TENCHI

354
00:13:50,291 --> 00:13:51,375
THAT DAY, DIDN'T IT?

355
00:13:51,458 --> 00:13:53,583
- WHAT DAY?
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

356
00:13:53,666 --> 00:13:56,208
- WE WERE RIGHT.  SOMETHING DID
HAPPEN THEN, DIDN'T IT?

357
00:13:56,291 --> 00:13:58,166
- I'M TELLING YOU,
I DON'T KNOW WHAT YOU MEAN.

358
00:13:58,250 --> 00:14:00,708
- WELL, I'M TALKING ABOUT
THE FESTIVAL THAT TOOK PLACE

359
00:14:00,791 --> 00:14:02,166
AT THE HIGH SCHOOL.

360
00:14:02,250 --> 00:14:03,875
- YEAH, WHAT ABOUT IT?

361
00:14:03,958 --> 00:14:05,875
- RYOKO, YOU MIGHT BE
A GOOD PIRATE,

362
00:14:05,958 --> 00:14:07,458
BUT YOU'RE A TERRIBLE LIAR.

363
00:14:07,541 --> 00:14:09,541
- ( scoffs )
AH, BACK OFF OR ELSE!

364
00:14:09,625 --> 00:14:11,416
- WHAT HAPPENED
WITH TENCHI THAT DAY?

365
00:14:11,500 --> 00:14:12,916
- EXCUSE ME, RYOKO.

366
00:14:13,000 --> 00:14:15,250
- HUH?
HEY, WHAT DO YOU WANT, MIHOSHI?

367
00:14:15,333 --> 00:14:17,208
- WHERE'S THE RESTROOM
IN THIS HIDEOUT?!

368
00:14:17,291 --> 00:14:19,250
- HUH?
- I'M DESPERATE, I TELL YOU.

369
00:14:19,333 --> 00:14:21,125
I'VE BEEN LOOKING AROUND
FOR THE LAST 10 MINUTES.

370
00:14:21,208 --> 00:14:22,875
OH!
- IT'S OFF THE ASSEMBLY HALL.

371
00:14:22,958 --> 00:14:24,416
- I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.
- ( both groan )

372
00:14:24,500 --> 00:14:26,416
- WOMAN IN TROUBLE.
GANGWAY, COMING THROUGH!

373
00:14:26,500 --> 00:14:28,208
( gasps )
- ( men chattering )

374
00:14:28,291 --> 00:14:30,000
- OH, NO.
THIS CAN'T BE HAPPENING.

375
00:14:30,083 --> 00:14:32,083
LOOK AT THE SIZE
OF THAT LINE.

376
00:14:32,166 --> 00:14:34,333
THERE MUST BE A WAY
TO SPEED THOSE PIRATES UP.

377
00:14:34,416 --> 00:14:37,333
OF COURSE!
I'LL GIVE THEM A HOT FOOT!

378
00:14:37,416 --> 00:14:39,000
FIRE!

379
00:14:41,291 --> 00:14:42,791
OOH!

380
00:14:44,833 --> 00:14:46,708
- ( screaming )

381
00:14:46,791 --> 00:14:48,291
- THANKS, I'LL BE RIGHT OUT.

382
00:14:48,375 --> 00:14:50,125
- CAN I CHANGE THE SUBJECT?

383
00:14:50,208 --> 00:14:51,250
- HMM?

384
00:14:51,333 --> 00:14:52,916
- WHY ARE YOU WITH
THIS GUY HOTSUMA?

385
00:14:53,000 --> 00:14:54,458
- AGAIN,
NONE OF YOUR BUSINESS.

386
00:14:54,541 --> 00:14:58,166
- Mihoshi: I'M BACK, LADIES.
BOY, WAS THAT A CLOSE CALL.

387
00:14:58,250 --> 00:15:00,791
- YOU GOTTA ADMIT, HE'S NO MATCH
FOR TENCHI NOW, IS HE?

388
00:15:00,875 --> 00:15:03,458
- YES, BUT TENCHI'S NOT
THE ONLY MAN IN THE WORLD.

389
00:15:03,541 --> 00:15:05,958
- I CAN'T BELIEVE YOU MEAN THAT.
- OH, BUT I DO.

390
00:15:06,041 --> 00:15:08,125
- WELL THEN, IF YOU'RE
OUT OF THE PICTURE,

391
00:15:08,208 --> 00:15:09,375
CAN I HAVE TENCHI?

392
00:15:09,458 --> 00:15:11,166
- OH MY, KIYONE.
DO YOU REALLY MEAN IT?

393
00:15:11,250 --> 00:15:12,791
YOU WANT TO MARRY TENCHI?
OOH!

394
00:15:12,875 --> 00:15:15,041
- HMM.  THIS DOESN'T
SOUND LIKE YOU AT ALL.

395
00:15:15,125 --> 00:15:17,041
- WELL, I THINK TENCHI
DESERVES A SOBER,

396
00:15:17,125 --> 00:15:18,916
LAW-ABIDING GIRL
LIKE MYSELF.

397
00:15:19,000 --> 00:15:20,375
A GIRL WHO'D BE
GOOD FOR HIM.

398
00:15:20,458 --> 00:15:22,500
- I HAVE A FEELING MIHOSHI
FRIED MORE THAN YOUR BUTT

399
00:15:22,583 --> 00:15:23,583
WHEN SHE BURNED YOU.

400
00:15:23,666 --> 00:15:24,791
ANYWAY, IT'S TOO LATE.

401
00:15:24,875 --> 00:15:25,958
WHEN I SAW THEM
THAT EVENING,

402
00:15:26,041 --> 00:15:27,541
TENCHI AND SAKUYA WERE--

403
00:15:27,625 --> 00:15:29,125
( sighs )

404
00:15:30,750 --> 00:15:32,416
- I WAS TRYING TO
GET HER TO OPEN UP,

405
00:15:32,500 --> 00:15:34,833
BUT THAT WORKED A WHOLE LOT
BETTER THAN I IMAGINED.

406
00:15:34,916 --> 00:15:36,833
- HMM.
- SO TENCHI AND SAKUYA

407
00:15:36,916 --> 00:15:38,375
HAD SOMETHING GOING
ON BETWEEN

408
00:15:38,458 --> 00:15:39,375
THEM DURING THE FESTIVAL?

409
00:15:39,458 --> 00:15:40,708
- Mihoshi:
WHAT WAS IT, EXACTLY?

410
00:15:40,791 --> 00:15:43,166
- Kiyone: I DON'T KNOW,
BUT THAT'S WHY RYOKO LEFT.

411
00:15:43,250 --> 00:15:45,666
- SHUT UP!
STOP ALL YOUR STUPID BABBLING.

412
00:15:45,750 --> 00:15:47,333
I DON'T CARE WHAT HAPPENED
BETWEEN THEM.

413
00:15:47,416 --> 00:15:49,083
I JUST WANT TO
FORGET ABOUT IT, ALL RIGHT?

414
00:15:49,166 --> 00:15:50,666
- YOU WANT TO
FORGET ABOUT EARTH?

415
00:15:50,750 --> 00:15:51,833
COME ON, RYOKO.

416
00:15:51,916 --> 00:15:53,833
THIS SPACE YOU HAD BUILT
IS A CARBON COPY

417
00:15:53,916 --> 00:15:56,000
OF THE LIVING ROOM
AT THE MASAKI HOUSE.

418
00:16:01,500 --> 00:16:04,166
YOU'VE BEEN TRYING VERY HARD
TO KEEP THOSE MEMORIES ALIVE.

419
00:16:04,250 --> 00:16:06,625
WHY DON'T YOU STOP FIGHTING
AND ADMIT IT?

420
00:16:08,250 --> 00:16:09,583
( grunts )
DON'T RUN AWAY.

421
00:16:09,666 --> 00:16:10,583
- PLEASE, RYOKO.

422
00:16:10,666 --> 00:16:13,041
- STOP FIGHTING
AND ADMIT WHAT?

423
00:16:13,125 --> 00:16:16,041
I DO JUST FINE.
I DON'T NEED ANYBODY.

424
00:16:16,125 --> 00:16:18,708
- THAT MAY BE TRUE, BUT ARE YOU
HAPPY WITH YOUR EMPTY LIFE,

425
00:16:18,791 --> 00:16:20,458
KICKING AROUND AIMLESSLY?

426
00:16:20,541 --> 00:16:23,000
- IT'S TOO LATE
TO GO BACK TO A NORMAL LIFE.

427
00:16:23,083 --> 00:16:24,458
THINGS HAVE
CHANGED TOO MUCH.

428
00:16:24,541 --> 00:16:26,875
- OH, BUT YOU HAVEN'T
CHANGED AT ALL, RYOKO.

429
00:16:26,958 --> 00:16:28,875
- YOU THINK SO?
- POSITIVE?

430
00:16:28,958 --> 00:16:31,208
LET'S DO SOMETHING FUN.
HOW ABOUT A GAME OF CARDS?

431
00:16:31,291 --> 00:16:33,750
- WHAT?  YOU BROUGHT CARDS
ON THIS MISSION?

432
00:16:36,958 --> 00:16:39,333
- ALL RIGHT.
IT'LL BE LIKE AT MASAKIS!

433
00:16:39,416 --> 00:16:40,916
- SORRY, RYOKO,

434
00:16:41,000 --> 00:16:43,375
BUT I CAN'T HAVE YOU CONSORTING
WITH THE GALAXY POLICE.

435
00:16:43,458 --> 00:16:45,166
I'M AFRAID I'LL HAVE TO
BREAK THIS UP.

436
00:16:46,541 --> 00:16:49,208
- CAPTAIN, WE JUST RECEIVED
AN ANONYMOUS CALL.

437
00:16:49,291 --> 00:16:50,916
ACCORDING TO HIS INFORMATION,

438
00:16:51,000 --> 00:16:52,250
RYOKO AND HER
BAND OF PIRATES

439
00:16:52,333 --> 00:16:54,250
ARE HIDING OUT AT
POINT TWO-ZERO-ZERO.

440
00:16:54,333 --> 00:16:56,500
- POINT TWO-ZERO-ZERO
IS THE SPOT WHERE OFFICERS

441
00:16:56,583 --> 00:16:58,583
MIHOSHI AND KIYONE
WENT UNDERCOVER.

442
00:16:58,666 --> 00:17:00,250
ALL RIGHT, MEN.
LET'S GET MOVING.

443
00:17:00,333 --> 00:17:01,541
WE'LL PROCEED THERE
IMMEDIATELY.

444
00:17:03,666 --> 00:17:05,916
- CAN'T USE THAT ONE.
WHAT WAS YOUR MISSION

445
00:17:06,000 --> 00:17:07,625
ACTUALLY SUPPOSED
TO ACCOMPLISH HERE?

446
00:17:07,708 --> 00:17:09,625
- WE WERE SUPPOSED TO
INFILTRATE YOUR GANG

447
00:17:09,708 --> 00:17:11,750
AND FIND THE LOCATION
OF YOUR SECRET HIDEOUT.

448
00:17:11,833 --> 00:17:13,708
AND REPORT TO
THE TASK FORCE CAPTAIN,

449
00:17:13,791 --> 00:17:15,166
THEN WE WERE SUPPOSED
TO KEEP YOU HERE

450
00:17:15,250 --> 00:17:16,750
UNTIL HIS UNITS ARRIVED.

451
00:17:16,833 --> 00:17:19,375
BUT I GUESS OUR ASSIGNMENT
WILL BE INCOMPLETE.

452
00:17:19,458 --> 00:17:20,916
WE HAVEN'T REPORTED.

453
00:17:21,000 --> 00:17:22,083
- ( laughs )

454
00:17:22,166 --> 00:17:24,083
IT WOULDN'T MATTER
IF YOU DID CALL THEM IN.

455
00:17:24,166 --> 00:17:25,375
YOU COULDN'T KEEP ME
HERE LONG ENOUGH

456
00:17:25,458 --> 00:17:27,041
FOR THOSE BOZOS
TO CATCH ME.

457
00:17:27,125 --> 00:17:28,375
- HMM.  ALL RIGHT.

458
00:17:28,458 --> 00:17:29,750
YOU GOT A FREE RIDE
ON THIS ONE.

459
00:17:29,833 --> 00:17:31,583
DON'T PUSH IT.
AHH.

460
00:17:31,666 --> 00:17:33,125
- YEAH, CIRCUS TRICKS.

461
00:17:33,208 --> 00:17:35,291
- I LOVE BEING WITH FRIENDS.
THIS IS NICE.

462
00:17:35,375 --> 00:17:37,625
EVEN THOUGH WE WERE
SEPARATED FOR A LONG TIME,

463
00:17:37,708 --> 00:17:39,791
WE PICKED OURSELVES UP
RIGHT WHERE WE LEFT OFF.

464
00:17:39,875 --> 00:17:42,333
- HMM.  HMM?

465
00:17:42,416 --> 00:17:44,083
( groans )
- ( giggles )

466
00:17:44,166 --> 00:17:46,416
- ( alarm blaring )

467
00:17:46,500 --> 00:17:48,000
- HEY, WHAT'S THAT?

468
00:17:48,083 --> 00:17:50,291
- RYOKO!
- WHAT'S GOING ON, HOTSUMA?

469
00:17:50,375 --> 00:17:52,125
- IT'S THE GALAXY POLICE.
THEY'RE HERE.

470
00:17:52,208 --> 00:17:54,458
- HUH?
OH, MY FRIENDS ARE COOL.

471
00:17:54,541 --> 00:17:55,625
DON'T WORRY ABOUT THEM.

472
00:17:55,708 --> 00:17:59,541
- OH, REALLY?
WELL LOOK AT THIS.

473
00:17:59,625 --> 00:18:02,000
- THAT'S THE TASK FORCE'S
NEW FLEET OF SPACE CRUISERS.

474
00:18:03,166 --> 00:18:04,791
- THIS IS THE GALAXY POLICE.

475
00:18:04,875 --> 00:18:06,666
RYOKO, YOU HAVE
NO PLACE TO RUN.

476
00:18:06,750 --> 00:18:08,291
SURRENDER AT ONCE
OR WE'LL ATTACK.

477
00:18:08,375 --> 00:18:09,625
THERE'LL BE
NO FURTHER WARNING.

478
00:18:09,708 --> 00:18:11,208
- ( watch beeping )

479
00:18:11,291 --> 00:18:13,125
- HMM?

480
00:18:13,208 --> 00:18:15,125
- DETECTIVES KIYONE
AND MIHOSHI,

481
00:18:15,208 --> 00:18:16,666
THIS IS TASK FORCE COMMAND.

482
00:18:16,750 --> 00:18:18,916
EXCELLENT JOB.
YOUR ASSIGNMENT IS COMPLETE.

483
00:18:19,000 --> 00:18:20,833
REPORT BACK TO HEADQUARTERS,
OVER.

484
00:18:20,916 --> 00:18:22,666
- KIYONE,
WHAT'S HAPPENING HERE?

485
00:18:22,750 --> 00:18:23,791
- UM...

486
00:18:23,875 --> 00:18:25,791
- ( scoffs )
VERY CLEVER, LADIES.

487
00:18:25,875 --> 00:18:28,125
- IT WASN'T US!
- STOP IT!

488
00:18:28,208 --> 00:18:30,041
YOU CALL YOURSELVES FRIENDS.

489
00:18:30,125 --> 00:18:33,500
THIS IS WHY I WENT BACK
TO BEING A SPACE PIRATE.

490
00:18:33,583 --> 00:18:35,333
SO I COULD DISRUPT THE WORLD

491
00:18:35,416 --> 00:18:37,291
THAT NASTY BACKSTABBERS
LIKE THE BOTH OF YOU

492
00:18:37,375 --> 00:18:38,500
WALK AROUND IN.

493
00:18:38,583 --> 00:18:40,833
- NO, WAIT!  WE REALLY
DIDN'T BRING THEM HERE.

494
00:18:40,916 --> 00:18:42,500
- WE'D BETTER SPLIT.

495
00:18:42,583 --> 00:18:44,916
- HMM.
- Mihoshi: RYOKO!

496
00:18:45,000 --> 00:18:47,375
- WAIT!  DON'T LEAVE!
WHAT ABOUT TENCHI?

497
00:18:47,458 --> 00:18:49,333
IS THIS WHAT
YOU REALLY WANT?

498
00:18:49,416 --> 00:18:51,041
YOU'RE NEVER GOING
BACK TO EARTH?

499
00:18:51,125 --> 00:18:52,500
- THAT'S HISTORY.

500
00:18:52,583 --> 00:18:53,708
- WE'VE GOT TO MOVE.

501
00:18:53,791 --> 00:18:55,583
- RYOKO...

502
00:18:55,666 --> 00:18:57,583
CAN'T WE TRY TO STOP HER,
KIYONE?

503
00:18:57,666 --> 00:18:58,875
- I CAN'T 'CAUSE I'M INJURED,

504
00:18:58,958 --> 00:18:59,875
SO I'LL HAVE TO
COUNT ON YOU.

505
00:18:59,958 --> 00:19:00,875
- RIGHT.

506
00:19:04,000 --> 00:19:06,166
- Hotsuma: LISTEN UP,
THERE'S NOTHING TO BE AFRAID OF.

507
00:19:06,250 --> 00:19:08,208
THE GALAXY POLICE ARE
A BUNCH OF PAPER TITLES.

508
00:19:08,291 --> 00:19:10,291
PROTECT THIS HIDEOUT
NO MATTER WHAT.

509
00:19:10,375 --> 00:19:11,875
- ( cheering )
- RYOKO, WAIT!

510
00:19:13,125 --> 00:19:15,375
PLEASE!
DON'T RUN AWAY FROM US.

511
00:19:15,458 --> 00:19:16,958
I'M SURE WE CAN
WORK THIS OUT.

512
00:19:17,041 --> 00:19:18,541
LET'S GO BACK TO EARTH
TOGETHER.

513
00:19:18,625 --> 00:19:20,833
- SORRY, MIHOSHI.
- PLEASE, RYOKO.

514
00:19:20,916 --> 00:19:22,541
WE'RE YOUR FRIENDS.
DON'T DO THIS.

515
00:19:22,625 --> 00:19:24,541
- YOU MEN KEEP HER
FROM GETTING ONBOARD.

516
00:19:26,583 --> 00:19:27,458
- ( sighs )

517
00:19:29,583 --> 00:19:31,333
- ( men shouting )

518
00:19:33,375 --> 00:19:36,041
- WHOA!
BACK OFF, YOU GUYS.

519
00:19:36,125 --> 00:19:39,291
DON'T COME NEAR
OR YOU'LL BE BARBEQUED!

520
00:19:41,833 --> 00:19:42,958
HERE COMES THE FIRE.

521
00:19:43,041 --> 00:19:44,000
- ( screaming )

522
00:19:45,166 --> 00:19:47,291
- YAH!

523
00:19:47,375 --> 00:19:48,625
- ( men scream )

524
00:19:49,750 --> 00:19:50,916
- HOW DO YOU LIKE
YOUR STEAKS?

525
00:19:51,000 --> 00:19:53,333
I CAN GIVE YOU WELL-DONE
OR MEDIUM-RARE!

526
00:19:53,416 --> 00:19:54,625
- ( screaming )

527
00:19:58,416 --> 00:19:59,458
- RYOKO...

528
00:20:11,208 --> 00:20:12,583
- THANKS, GIRLS,

529
00:20:12,666 --> 00:20:14,583
FOR REMINDING ME
OF ANOTHER LIFE.

530
00:20:18,708 --> 00:20:21,041
- YOU SEE, YOU APPLY
THIS FORMULA TO THIS ONE,

531
00:20:21,125 --> 00:20:23,041
AND THERE YOU HAVE
YOUR SOLUTION.

532
00:20:23,125 --> 00:20:24,250
- YOU MAKE IT
SOUND SO EASY.

533
00:20:24,333 --> 00:20:25,708
NOW I KNOW WHERE
I WENT WRONG.

534
00:20:25,791 --> 00:20:26,958
YOU'RE BRILLIANT, TENCHI.

535
00:20:27,041 --> 00:20:28,958
- IF YOU VALEDICTORIANS
CAN STOP WRITING

536
00:20:29,041 --> 00:20:31,791
YOUR SPEECHES FOR A SECOND,
SOMEONE NEEDS HELP.

537
00:20:31,875 --> 00:20:33,916
- SO FAR, I'M FAILING
EVERY SUBJECT.

538
00:20:34,000 --> 00:20:35,958
AND I'VE GOT THREE
MAKE-UP TESTS TO TAKE.

539
00:20:36,041 --> 00:20:37,958
- I GUESS HE'S GOING
TO SUMMER SCHOOL.

540
00:20:38,041 --> 00:20:39,708
HE'S GONNA MISS
THE WHOLE BREAK.

541
00:20:39,791 --> 00:20:41,500
- I CAN'T GET STUCK
IN SUMMER SCHOOL!

542
00:20:41,583 --> 00:20:43,791
I WANNA GO ON A TRIP
WITH EVERYONE ELSE!

543
00:20:43,875 --> 00:20:45,916
- I'LL HELP TUTOR YOU.

544
00:20:46,000 --> 00:20:47,625
- TENCHI'S AMAZING,
ISN'T HE?

545
00:20:47,708 --> 00:20:49,166
- YEAH, HE'S A GOOD TEACHER.

546
00:20:49,250 --> 00:20:51,125
HE'S GOT SIMPLE
EXPLANATIONS FOR EVERYTHING.

547
00:20:51,208 --> 00:20:54,125
- HE CAN EVEN TEACH AMAGASAKI,
WHO NEVER UNDERSTANDS ANYTHING.

548
00:20:54,208 --> 00:20:56,291
- AND AT THE SCHOOL FESTIVAL,
HE HELPED US PUT UP THE BOOTH

549
00:20:56,375 --> 00:20:57,375
AND SOLD RAFFLE TICKETS.

550
00:20:57,458 --> 00:20:58,916
- SAKUYA'S SO LUCKY.

551
00:20:59,000 --> 00:21:01,333
- I BET YOU'D GO OUT WITH TENCHI
IN A MINUTE IF HE ASKED YOU.

552
00:21:01,416 --> 00:21:03,500
- OF COURSE NOT.
HE'S DATING SAKUYA,

553
00:21:03,583 --> 00:21:05,500
SO IT WOULD NEVER
COME UP, WOULD IT?

554
00:21:05,583 --> 00:21:07,833
- Sakuya: TENCHI,
YOU'RE A PRETTY AMAZING GUY.

555
00:21:07,916 --> 00:21:09,750
I WANT TO LEARN
A LOT MORE ABOUT YOU.

556
00:21:09,833 --> 00:21:12,000
I JUST HOPE YOU FEEL
THE SAME WAY ABOUT ME.

557
00:21:12,083 --> 00:21:13,333
- HUH?

558
00:21:13,416 --> 00:21:15,083
TSUGARU, MATORI,

559
00:21:15,166 --> 00:21:18,500
WELL, I REALLY DON'T
UNDERSTAND WHAT SHE'S THINKING.

560
00:21:27,583 --> 00:21:29,000
- HMM?

561
00:21:31,041 --> 00:21:33,583
- WHATEVER'S ON YOUR MIND,
YOU CAN JUST FORGET IT.

562
00:21:35,583 --> 00:21:37,458
( laughs )

563
00:21:44,291 --> 00:21:46,166
- ( theme music playing )

564
00:22:05,958 --> 00:22:07,833
- ( singing in Japanese )

565
00:23:03,791 --> 00:23:06,375
- ( meows )

566
00:23:09,375 --> 00:23:10,291
( meows )

567
00:23:12,416 --> 00:23:14,208
- Mihoshi:
HI, IT'S ME, MIHOSHI.

568
00:23:14,291 --> 00:23:15,958
LISTEN, WE'VE BEEN
DOING SO WELL

569
00:23:16,041 --> 00:23:18,250
THAT G.P. HEADQUARTERS
FINALLY REWARDED US

570
00:23:18,333 --> 00:23:19,416
WITH A MEDAL.

571
00:23:19,500 --> 00:23:21,958
I BET TENCHI WILL BE
VERY EXCITED FOR US.

572
00:23:22,041 --> 00:23:23,958
IF ONLY WE HAD A CHANCE
TO TELL HIM.

573
00:23:24,041 --> 00:23:26,625
IT MUST BE SUMMER NOW
BACK ON EARTH.

574
00:23:26,708 --> 00:23:29,458
KIYONE, DON'T WE HAVE
A SUMMER VACATION?

575
00:23:29,541 --> 00:23:31,875
IF WE DO, I THINK I'LL LIKE
TO TAKE A TRIP TO EARTH

576
00:23:31,958 --> 00:23:33,875
TO SEE TENCHI.

577
00:23:33,958 --> 00:23:36,916
THE NEXT EPISODE OF
THE NEW TENCHI MUYO SERIES...

